<problem>
<variantControl nVariants='1' />
<!-- <title>Cobweb linear approx: linear dynamical system with constant</title>
 -->
<setup>

<math name='one' simplify='full' >1</math>
<math name='E' simplify='full' >c/(1-b)</math>
<math name='zero' simplify='full' >0</math>
<math name='n1' simplify='full' >-1</math>
<math name='E_b_n1' simplify='full' >c/2</math>

</setup>

  
<p>If we add a constant term to the linear discrete dynamical system, we get a dynamical system of the form
  <me>y_{n+1} = b y_n + c, \quad \text{for $ n=0,1,2,\ldots $ }</me>
where <m>b</m> and <m>c</m> are parameters, which can be positive or negative.</p>

  
<p>To answer the questions, you can use this cobweb applet, where you can change the value of the parameters <m>b</m> and <m>c</m>.</p>

  
<p>b = <mathinput prefill="1/2" name="b" /></p>
<p>c = <mathinput prefill="1" name="c" /></p>

<function hide name="byc" variables="y_n" simplify>$b y_n + $c</function>

<p>Cobweb applet for
  <me>y_{n+1} = $byc</me>
</p>

  <setup>
    <function name="f" symbolic>$formula</function>
    <solveEquations variables="x" name="solveForE" minVar="$xmin" maxVar="$xmax">$formula = x</solveEquations>
    <copy prop="x" tname="A" assignNames='px' />
    <derivative name="df">$f</derivative>
    <number name="nPoints">10</number>
    <number name="zeroFixed" fixed>0</number>
    <point x="-5" y="$(initialPoint{prop='x'})" name="initialPoint" hide>
      <constraints>
        <constrainToGraph />
      </constraints>
    </point>

    <number fixed name="xmin">-10</number>
    <number fixed name="xmax">10</number>

  </setup>

  <updateValue label="Add line" name="addLine" tname="nPoints" newValue="$nPoints+1" type="number" />
  <updateValue label="Delete line" name="deleteLine" tname="nPoints" newValue="$nPoints-1" type="number" disabled="$nPoints <= 1" />

  <graph xlabel="y_n" ylabel="y_{n+1}" identicalAxisScales grid  showNavigation="false" xmin="$xmin" xmax="$xmax" ymin="$xmin" ymax="$xmax">

    <cobwebpolyline function="$byc" nPoints="$nPoints" name="cobwebPolyline" initialPoint="$initialPoint" lockToSolution draggable="false" />
    <copy tname="initialPoint" layer="2" />
  </graph>

  <aside name="calculatedValue">
    <title>Calculated values</title>

    <md>
    <map>
      <template>
        <mrow>
          y_{<number>$i-1</number>} \amp = $(x{displayDigits="5"})
        </mrow>
      </template>
      <sources alias="x" indexAlias="i">
        <copy prop="iterateValues" tname="cobwebPolyline" />
      </sources>
    </map>
    </md>

  </aside>


  
<ol>

<li>
<p>
What condition on the parameter <m>b</m> will ensure there is exactly one equilibrium?  <m>b \ne</m> 
<answer>
<award symbolicEquality='true' simplifyOnCompare='numbers'>$one </award>
</answer>

</p>
<p>

Given that condition, what is the equilibrium? <m>E=</m> 
<answer>
<award>$E </award>
</answer>

</p>
<p>

The value of this equilibrium 
<answer inline='true'>
<choiceinput>
<choice credit='1'>does</choice>
<choice>does not</choice>
</choiceinput>
</answer>
