</p>

</li>

<li>
<p>
How does the behavior of the dynamical system depend on the sign of <m>b</m>?  On the sign of <m>c</m>?
</p>
<p>

When <m>b</m> is negative, the solution 
<answer inline='true'>
<choiceinput>
<choice credit='1'>spirals around</choice>
<choice>moves steadily toward or away from</choice>
</choiceinput>
</answer>
 the equilibrium.
</p>
<p>

When <m>b</m> is positive, the solution 
<answer inline='true'>
<choiceinput>
<choice credit='1'>moves steadily toward or away from</choice>
<choice>spirals around</choice>
</choiceinput>
</answer>
 the equilibrium.
</p>
<p>

The behavior of the solution 
<answer inline='true'>
<choiceinput>
<choice credit='1'>does not</choice>
<choice>does</choice>
</choiceinput>
</answer>
